cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM

The paper proposes a machine learning approach for the interpretation of mFISH images using convolutional neural networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of machine learning algorithms for image analysis and diagnosis of genetic diseases suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of imaging techniques, which could place it under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of fluorescent probes and imaging techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
